reator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131460184,imgsize-901943.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Paper Cup King: Indian man sets Guinness World Record with 858 paper cups from 31 countries]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131460142.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/paper-cup-king-indian-man-sets-world-record-for-collecting-858-unique-paper-cups-from-31-countries/articleshow/131460142.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/paper-cup-king-indian-man-sets-world-record-for-collecting-858-unique-paper-cups-from-31-countries/articleshow/131460142.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-02T14:59:38+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131460210,imgsize-1630799.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Britain’s oldest known prehistoric art confirmed in Derbyshire Cave, dating back more than 13,000 years]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131459925.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Ancient markings in a Derbyshire cave, once dismissed as mere scratches, are now confirmed as Britain's oldest prehistoric art.  Scientific analysis reveals these deliberate carvings, dating back 13,000 to 15,000 years, offer a rare glimpse into the creative expression of Ice Age hunter-gatherers, rewriting our understanding of early British culture.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/britains-oldest-known-prehistoric-art-confirmed-in-derbyshire-cave-dating-back-more-than-13000-years/articleshow/131459925.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.